.//     All rights reserved.
.//============================================================================
.//
.//============================================================================
.// Notes:
.// (1) Marking is specified via archetype function invocation(s) in this file.
.//     A function invocation statement MUST be specified on a single line.
.//     All indicated function input parameters must be supplied.
.// (2) All quoted string parameters are case sensitive.
.// (3) Comments in this file start with ".//".
.// (4) Do not leave any blank lines in this file.
.//============================================================================
.//
.//
.//============================================================================
.// Wire Bridge Between xtUML Domains using Synchronous Services:
.//
.// To connect two xtUML domains using Synchronous Services, use the following
.// mark:
.//
.//   WireSynchServiceOoaBridge( "initiating_dom", "ee_key_letters", "recipient_dom" )
.//
.// Where the input parameters are:
.//   initiating_dom = Registered name of the Initiating Domain.
.//   ee_key_letters = Key letters of the External Entity in the Initiating Domain.
.//   recipient_dom  = Registered name of the Recipient Domain.
.//  
.// Notes:
.// (1) The term "Initiating Domain" refers to the xtUML domain which contains
.//     the External Entity (EE) against which Bridge calls (to the recipient
.//     domain) are made.
.// (2) The term "Recipient Domain" refers to the xtUML domain which provides
.//     the Synchronous Services.
.// (3) This type of bridging supports the use of Reference Parameters in the
.//     External Entity and Synchronous Services of the analysis models.
.//
.// Example:
.//   .invoke WireSynchServiceOoaBridge( "HOME", "WAY_EE", "AWAY" )
.//
.//============================================================================
.//
.//
.//============================================================================
.// Wire Bridge Between xtUML domain and Realized Domain:
.//
.// WireRealizedExternalEntity( "ooa_domain_name", "ee_key_letters",
.//                "realized_domain_name", "method_prefix", "include_file" )
.//
.// Where the input parameters are:
.//  ooa_domain_name = Registered name of xtUML Domain. ("*" means any domain)
.//  ee_key_letters = Key letters of the External Entity in the xtUML Domain(s).
.//  realized_domain_name = Registered name of Realized Domain
.//  method_prefix = A prefix to be prepended to the bridge process method name
.//    used in the BridgePoint action language.
.//
.//  include_file = Name of the header file to include for the realized domain.
.//
.// Example:
.//  .invoke WireRealizedExternalEntity( "ODMS", "PIO", "PIO", "PIO", "PIO_bridge.h" )
.//
.//============================================================================
.//
.//
.//============================================================================
.// Mark Synchronous Service as Safe for Interrupt Execution:
.//
.// To indicate to the model compiler that a synchronous service
.// may be invoked in a manner safe for invocation from an interrupt
.// handler or other asynchronous activation (one for each synchronous
.// service):
.//
.// TagSyncServiceSafeForInterrupts( "domain", "sync_service" )
.//
.// Where the input parameters are:
.//   domain = registered xtUML domain name
.//   sync_service = name of synchronous service
.//
.// Example:
.//  .invoke TagSyncServiceSafeForInterrupts( "ILB", "PumpReady" )
.//
.//============================================================================
